               <p>I <rs id="t17810711-28-viclabel152" type="occupation">keep an hotel</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17810711-28-victim525 t17810711-28-viclabel152"></join>, in <placeName id="t17810711-28-crimeloc153">Covent-garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17810711-28-crimeloc153" type="placeName" value="Covent-garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17810711-28-crimeloc153" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17810711-28-off150 t17810711-28-crimeloc153"></join>. The prisoner came to sleep one night, at one o'clock.</p>

               <p>A Witness sworn.</p>

               <p>The prisoner came down in the morning, and asked, What was to pay? I said, I would let him know, if he would walk into the parlour. I went up stairs, and found the bed stripped. I halloo'd out, to let them know the things were gone. The prisoner came up, and threw the things down upon the bed. I met him at the door: just as I was coming out of the room, he went in. I came down stairs immediately, and told my master and the people in the house of it. When I came up again, the things were found upon the bed, folded up.</p>

               <p>Were they upon the bed when you went in first? - No.</p>

               <p>Did nobody go up but him? - No: I left him in the room, and came down. He wanted to push by me, to get into the room: I screamed out, and said the bed was stripped.</p>

               <p>Prisoner. I am guilty of the fact.</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t17810711-28-verdict154" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17810711-28-verdict154" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>

               <p>Tried by the Second Middlesex Jury, before Mr. Justice BULLER.</p>
